OL,3,CPembrokeshire Council says it won't
OL,4,Cintroduce tourism tax for at least two
OL,5,Cyears
OL,7,FPembrokeshire Council has said it will
OL,8,Fnot introduce a tourism tax until at
OL,9,Fleast the next council term in May
OL,10,F2027.
OL,12,FThe Welsh Government is introducing
OL,13,Fthe proposed visitor levy, which would
OL,14,Fsee visitors charged up to #1.30 per
OL,15,Fovernight stay (excluding children),
OL,16,Fwhich passed its first vote in the
OL,17,FSenedd on 1 April.
OL,19,FEven if the proposals are approved, it
OL,20,Fwill be up to Welsh councils to decide
OL,21,Fif they implement the charge.
