OL,3,CPembrokeshire Council says it won't
OL,4,Cintroduce tourism tax for at least two
OL,5,Cyears
OL,7,FOn April 1, Wales' finance minister
OL,8,FMark Drakeford introduced the visitor
OL,9,Flevy for its first vote. At the same
OL,10,Ftime he announced children would be
OL,11,Fexempt from the charge in most
OL,12,Faccommodations but that as a result
OL,13,Finitial nightly costs would increase.
OL,15,FFor areas which choose to introduce
OL,16,Fthe charge, guests staying at hotels,
OL,17,FB&Bs and self-catered accommodation
OL,18,Fwould pay #1.30 per night, up from the
OL,19,Finitial #.125 proposed, while hostel
OL,20,Fand campsite guests would pay 80p, up
OL,21,Ffrom an initial 75p.
